==English==
===Verb===
'''frenched'''  past tense

# cooking term, to cut into strips
#: You make [[french fries]] from potatoes that have been '''frenched'''.
# to have been [[french kiss]]ed <!--does this french get capitalized?-->
#: ''He '''frenched''' me...and I liked it.''

*''Usage note:'' The cooking term is not inherently capitalized because it has lost its relation to the country France over the years.